<br>
Please, bare with me, it is important to understand <i><b>why</i></b> I decided to shoot for this <i><b>before</b></i> we start coming up with things that may stray from it's purpose...<br>
<br>
<br>
Many MANY people would claim:<br>
<br>
<center><h4><font color="#FF0000"><b>ROLEPLAY IS DEAD.</center></h4></font></b><br>
<br>
It has been my experience that when churches feel the need to boost spiritual morale, they hold <b>REVIVALS</b>.  Souls are saved, demons are called out, etc etc.  <b><i>And that's what I want this to be</i></b>, a RP revival even if it is only for one night - so I'd like it to be near outrageous (not impossible) and as true to RP as possible and something FUN, and EXCITING that will bring good together with good, evil together with evil, and perhaps rekindle that fire that so many people insist is slowly going out.<br>
<br>
Now, with that in mind I would like to say that Ezra, you read my mind.  That is exactly the TYPE of thing I was thinking. Mawg, we would not actually be KILLING a god, but possess the power to do so.  If good can not stop evil then we COULD kill the god, hence the "effect" of the weapon, and then it can just be assumed that that is what happened.<br>
<br>
The event would be the RP, questing and fighting.<br>
<br>
The event's story line would be the plot to take down a god. (no, this is NOT set in stone)<br>
<br>
<b><i>If good guys do not show up to save the day</b></i>, then Evil wins and it should go down in the history of the EMarr server as such... until there is a day that good regroups and can take back what we have stolen, and return to the EMarr server it's Valor, Honor, Courage, Love and whatever else.  The same applies if Evil does not show up to do their thing, though from the looks of things, Evil is more than ready to act on this. =)<br>
<br>
This could involve evil questing for <b>God Slayer</b>, good questing for it's nullifier which I will call <b>Whoop Arse</b> for the moment, and then boil down to a <b>Battle Royale</b> that can be held in one of many different ways, in which the final stages of the Event will take place.<br>
<br>
I will continue to ask the guides questions on what we can and cannot do as they appear in response to this post.<br>
<br>
I would like to take a poll of what people would like to see happen and what they would like to do, but it seems polls aren't allowed on this board.  Any suggestions? =)<br>
<br>
I would also like to spread word of this.  Anyone willing to help?<br>
<br>
