Children of Darkness</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufrittitailchaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritti Tailchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/29/01 12:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrroleplayingoocforum.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=61.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bonk HEY RP GUILDS</span><hr size=1> I don't roleplay in EverQuest. Let's be honest, it's not designed for it. This isn't a MUSH. The roleplay I've seen on EverQuest (no offense intended) isn't all that great. <br>
<br>
But, I follow the roleplaying forum, mostly. I saw this post and felt I should give my little bit of imput, for what it is (or isn't) worth.<br>
<br>
The less you involve Guides/GMs in this, the better. If you're relying on them to do anything, you're going to be hard pressed to have them commit to a day. Additionally, if their attendance falls through, then you're stuck waiting for their assistance which won't be forthcoming. ESPECIALLY if you're asking them to create something (an item, I gathered from where this thread seemed to be going). <br>
<br>
If you want my advice (which I'm sure you don't), I'd suggest you go and find a MUSH (I'd suggest AmberMUSH - the storyline is somewhat familiar if you've read the Roger Zelazny novels) and watch their plots for a bit. Consider the following suggestions:<br>
<br>
1. King of Felwithe/Queen of Neriak is dying and need X elixir/item/person in the possession/prisoner of the opposing force (easy enough to make an anon LV1 character for this, and someone pass them some armour, to make them look the part).<br>
<br>
2. The oppressive (insert NPC race here) has driven both X and Y past the breaking point. They find they must ally to vanquish the foe (for example, the Froglok King is a likely target, or Zalgoz of Kaesora). <br>
<br>
3. The oppressive (insert NPC race here) has driven both X and Y past the breaking point. They do not need to ally to vanquish the foe, and a race ensues for who can kill the most NPC race (Splitpaw, Permafrost, Droga, Nurga would be excellent for this sort of thing). <br>
<br>
4. Instead of god slaying, a best of the best between you. Have it much like the BotB trials thusfar - the evil champions fight it out between each other, the same with the good champions. Then the final struggle between the good and evil champion, with the winner gaining possession of the loser's weapon (make it something easily replaceable, or plan ahead of time and camp something specifically for the purpose). <br>
<br>
5. Romeo &amp; Juliet it - or Beauty &amp; the Beast it. Opposing evil/good fall in love, and the &quot;parents&quot; have to come and stop the wedding. <br>
<br>
I wish you luck. I don't think roleplaying is dead. It's just not found much on EverQuest.<br>
<br>
-FT<br>
