<br>
Anything I can do whatsoever at all, even if it requires huge amounts of time and means I don't get to camp anything at all ever again I will do if it means I can roleplay on EQ. &lt;remembers who is present&gt; Well just about anything.<br>
<br>
I think it would be fanstastic to try start a large roleplay plot, and even better if we can get GM help, I do agree that we need to limit this to a really small thing, we don't want to scare the poor little GM creatures on their first outing with the roleplayers.<br>
<br>
How about we do a large plot in stages, a series of events. That way we get to see how it goes, if it falls flat fair enough, if it works then maybe we can build the GMs up to doing something more funky. As far as I've seen the GMs don't mind: shouting things across zones in the guise of random npcs, occasionally popping into the bodies of npcs, turning the sky a funny colour (whether deliberately or not) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This is an idea I had a while back: The evil gods got stuck behind a wall, put up by the other gods because they were bad, right? The only way for evil to dominate once more is to lower this wall. I figured there could be things upon our plane that could cause this to happen: seals if you will. There would be several of these seals, and it would be the job of the evillies to break them, and the job of the goodites to protect them. This, I thought could incorporate both ritual (nice bit of roleplay, perhaps item gathering), and fighting (to break up the rituals). The plus point to this idea is that there could be so many seals we would never necessarily break them all, meaning there was no permanent irreversable effect to the battle between good and evil (which is just as bad for roleplay...oh we won, erm...tum te tum...tea anyone?) If we pull off a ritual perhaps the sky could go red, something could go bang and a scary voice could shout stuff...if not we get to have a good scrap. We could also use lots of bizarre out of the way locations for this, like the litch tunnels in Everfrost: it's scary down there!<br>
<br>
On the subject of mixers, I would love to have a game of corspe football. I found out a little while ago that you can consent more than one person at a time to drag a corpse. You can 'steal' the corpse from another consented person and run off with it, and so on. We could do this in teams, perhaps in the arena, scoring points for each time a team gets the corspe to their side, or goal area. The only thing to check is how many people can be consented at one time. I suppose the other question is, would we play clean or dirty rules...fear anyone? Anyway, this is so funny, I recommend trying it with a dead friend or two! <br>
<br>
Finally, I would just like to say WAR.<br>
<br>
That's my two-pence worth,<br>
<br>
Take care all,<br>
<br>
Kaidal. <br>
